Collective Diffusion Coefficient of Million Molecular Weight Polymer Is Comparable to That of a Sodium Ion. In salt-free polyelectrolyte solutions, we expect the hydrodynamic radius Rh of a chain to be proportional to N, and hence
the diffusion coefficient DSE according to the Stokes−Einstein (SE) law is expected to obey
